\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship ran aground off Beaumaris. She was on a voyage from [[Runcorn]], [[Cheshire]] to [[Porthdinllaen]], [[Caernarfonshire]]. She was wrecked in a gale on 19 January. Her crew were rescued.<ref name=Times240163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''John Williams'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[brig]] foundered in the [[Bay of Biscay]]. Her crew were rescued by the brig ''Alli'' ({{flagcountry|Russian Empire}}). ''John Williams'' was on a voyage from [[Newcastle upon Tyne]], [[Northumberland]] to [[Lisbon]], Portugal.<ref name=DN170163>{{Cite news |title=(untitled) |newspaper=Daily News |location=London |date=17 January 1863 |issue=5208 }}</ref><ref name=DC170163>{{Cite news |title=Dundee Shipping |newspaper=Dundee Courier |location=Dundee |date=17 January 1863 |issue=2945 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Ouse'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[steamship]] ran aground at [[Drag\u00f8r]], Denmark. She was on a  voyage from [[danzig|Dantzic]] to [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]], [[East Riding of Yorkshire|Yorkshire]].<ref name=DC080163>{{Cite news |title=Shipping Intelligence |newspaper=Dundee Courier |location=Dundee |date=8 January 1863 |issue=2938 }}</ref> She was refloated and taken in to [[Copenhagen]], Denmark.<ref name=S100163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Sanders''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was abandoned in the [[Bay of Biscay]] in a sinking condition. She was on a voyage from [[London]] to [[Genoa]] and [[Livorno]], [[Kingdom of Italy|Italy]].<ref name=Times230163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==9 January==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=9 January 1863 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Amaranth''\n|flag={{flag|Prussia|civil}}\n|desc=The [[brig]] was driven ashore at [[Kingsdown, Kent]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]]. She was refloated and taken in to [[Ramsgate]], Kent.<ref name=Times100163a/><ref 