ee Courier |location=Dundee |date=8 January 1863 |issue=2938 }}</ref> She was refloated and taken in to [[Copenhagen]], Denmark.<ref name=S100163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Sanders''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was abandoned in the [[Bay of Biscay]] in a sinking condition. She was on a voyage from [[London]] to [[Genoa]] and [[Livorno]], [[Kingdom of Italy|Italy]].<ref name=Times230163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==9 January==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=9 January 1863 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Amaranth''\n|flag={{flag|Prussia|civil}}\n|desc=The [[brig]] was driven ashore at [[Kingsdown, Kent]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]]. She was refloated and taken in to [[Ramsgate]], Kent.<ref name=Times100163a/><ref name=NC160163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Grunhorst'' \n|flag=[[File:Merchant Ensign of Holstein-Gottorp (Lions sinister).svg|22px]] [[Duchy of Holstein]] \n|desc=The [[galiot]] was driven ashore in the [[eider (river)|Eider]]. She was on a voyage from [[Newcastle upon Tyne]], [[Northumberland]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] to [[Delve]]. She was refloated and taken in to [[T\u00f6nning]] in a severely leaky condition.<ref name=NC160163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Herman'' \n|flag={{flag|Hamburg|admiralty}}\n|desc=The ship ran aground on the Longsand, in the [[North Sea]] off the coast of [[Essex]], United Kingdom. She was on a voyage from Hamburg to [[Saint Thomas, U.S. Virgin Islands|Saint Thomas]], [[Virgin Islands]]. She was refloated and taken in to [[Sheerness]]], [[Kent]], United Kingdom in a leaky condition.<ref name=S130163>{{Cite news |title=Mercantile Ship News |newspaper=The Standard |location=London |date=13 January 1863 |issue=11988 |page=7 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Marie'' \n|flag={{flag|Norway|1844}}\n|desc=The [[schooner]] ran aground on the Herd Sand, in the North Sea off the coast of [