iverpool |date=19 January 1863 |issue=4662 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Thames''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[collier (ship type)|collier]] collided with ''Hebe'' ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}})  and foundered in the [[North Sea]] off [[Cromer]], [[Norfolk]]. Her crew were rescued by ''Hebe''.<ref name=Times200163/><ref name=Times220163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==18 January==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=18 January 1863 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Anna Catharina''\n|flag={{flag|Netherlands}}\n|desc=The ship struck the [[Kentish Knock (England)|Kentish Knock]] and was wrecked. Her crew were rescued. She was on a voyage from [[Amsterdam]], [[North Holland]] to [[Surinam (Dutch colony)|Surinam]].<ref name=Times200163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Temperance'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was wrecked at [[Penmaenmawr]], [[Caernarfonshire]]. SHe was on a voyage from [[Liverpool]], [[Lancashire]] to [[Menai Bridge]], [[Anglesey]].<ref name=LM210163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Tropic''\n|flag={{flag|Confederate States of America|1861}}\n|desc=[[American Civil War]], [[Union blockade]]: The 323-ton sidewheel [[paddle steamer]], carrying a cargo of [[cotton]] and [[turpentine]], was destroyed by an accidental fire while attempting to [[Blockade runners of the American Civil War|run the Union blockade]] at [[Charleston, South Carolina]], [[Confederate States of America]]. Her passengers and crew were rescued by the armed sidewheel [[paddle steamer]] {{USS|Quaker City|1854|6}} ({{navy|United States|1861}}).<ref name=usnlpcivilwarchronologyJanJun1863/><ref>[https://www.history.navy.mil/content/history/nhhc/research/histories/ship-histories/confederate_ships/huntress.html Naval History and Heritage Command: Confederate Ships: Huntress]</ref><ref name=gainesp156>Gaines, p. 156.</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Tyne''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship struck 