yage from [[Middlesbrough]], [[North Riding of Yorkshire|Yorkshire]] to [[Dunkerque]], [[Nord (departements)|Nord]], France.<ref name=Times270163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Mary''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship foundered in the [[North Sea]] off [[Great Yarmouth]], [[Norfolk]]. Her crew were rescued. She was on a voyage from [[Blyth, Northumberland]] to [[Rochester, Kent]].<ref name=Times040263/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Medea''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[barque]] was driven ashore and wrecked at Penrhyn Point, [[Anglesey]]. Her crew were rescued by the Holyhead Lifeboat. She was on a voyage from the Cameroons, Africa to [[Liverpool]], [[Lancashire]].<ref name=Times210163>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Violent Storm |date=20 January 1863 |page_number=12 |issue=24461 |column=F }}</ref><ref name=Times220163a/><ref name=DN200163/><ref name=LM210163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Mudlark'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The unmanned [[dredger]] sank in a [[squall]] at [[Portsmouth]], [[Hampshire]].<ref name=DN200163>{{Cite news |title=Severe Gale |newspaper=Daily News |location=London |date=20 January 1863 |issue=5211 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Naples Packet''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[collier (ship)|collier]] collided with ''George Hughes'' ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}) and was abandoned in the [[North Sea]] off [[Aldeburgh]], [[Suffolk]]. She was on a voyage from [[South Shields]], [[County Durham]] to [[Rochester, Kent]].<ref name=Times220163/><ref name=Times220163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Sabrina''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore at Horse Head, [[County Cork]]. She was on a voyage from [[Cork (city)|Cork]] to [[Bristol]], [[Gloucestershire]].<ref name=Times240163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Sea Swallow''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[barque]] foundered in the 