hip was driven ashore on the [[Mull of Galloway]], [[Wigtownshire]]. Her crew were rescued. She was on a voyage from [[Alexandria]], [[Egypt Eyalet|Egypt]] to the [[River Clyde|Clyde]].<ref name=Times230163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Jane Storer''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[full-rigged ship]] was driven ashore and wrecked near [[Waterloo, Lancashire]] with the loss of two of her seventeen crew. She was on a voyage from [[Portland, Maine]] to [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]], [[East Riding of Yorkshire|Yorkshire]].<ref name=Times220163a/><ref name=Times310163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''John H. Elliott''\n|flag={{flag|United States|1861}}\n|desc=The [[full-rigged ship]] ran aground on the Burbo Bank and broke her back. Her crew were rescued by the [[tugboat|tug]] ''Reliance'' ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}). ''John H. Elliott''' was on a voyage from Liverpool to [[New York City|New York]].<ref name=Times220163>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Ship News |date=22 January 1863 |page_number=12 |issue=24462 |column=C }}</ref><ref name=Times220163a/><ref name=DN200163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Kezia''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[schooner]] was driven ashore and wrecked at [[Great Yarmouth]], [[Norfolk]]. She was on a voyage from [[Sunderland, County Durham]] to [[Caen]], [[Calvados (department)|Calvados]], France.<ref name=Times220163a>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=The Gale |date=22 January 1863 |page_number=12 |issue=24462 |column=E }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Lady Vaughan''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was abandoned in the North Sea {{convert|21|nmi|km}} off [[Ostend]], [[West Flanders]], Belgium. Her crew were rescued by a Belgian fishing vessel. She was on a voyage from Sunderland to [[Saint-Malo]], [[Ille-et-Vilaine]], France.<ref name=Times290163a>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Ship News |date=29 January 1863 |page_number=11 |issue=2446