20163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Rubin''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[barque]] ran aground on the Salthouse Bank, in the [[Irish Sea]]] off the coast of Lancashire. Her crew were rescued by the Lytham Lifeboat. ''Rubin'' was on a voyage from \"Woodpoint\" to [[Glasson Dock]], Lancashire. She subsequently floated off and was wrecked on the Horse Bank.<ref name=Times220163/><ref name=Times220163a/><ref name=Times230163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Spinner''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore at [[Formby]], Lancashire. She was on a voyage from [[Sagua la Grande]], [[Captaincy General of Cuba|Cuba]] to the [[River Clyde|Clyde]].<ref name=Times230163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Unity''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was discovered derelict off [[Margate]], [[Kent]]. She was taken in to Margate.<ref name=Times220163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Wilhelmina''\n|flag={{flag|Netherlands}}\n|desc=The ship was drive ashore on [[Vlieland]], [[Friesland]] with the loss of two of her crew. She was on a voyage from [[Groningen (city)|Groningen]] to London.<ref name=Times240163/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=Unidentified schooner\n|flag=Unknown\n|desc=American Civil War, Union blockade: The [[schooner]], a [[Blockade runners of the American Civil War|blockade runner]] heavily laden with supplies, was forced aground at [[New Topsail Inlet]] or [[Stump Inlet]] (sources disagree) on the coast of [[North Carolina]], Confederate States of Ameriac by the armed [[screw steamer]] {{USS|Daylight|1859|6}} ({{navy|United States|1861}}). She then was wrecked by [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]] gunfire, taking 20 to 25 shell hits.<ref name=usnlpcivilwarchronologyJanJun1863/><ref name=gainesp132>Gaines, p. 132.</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==22 January==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=22 January 1863|sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Congress''\n|flag={{flagcou