t-Valery-sur-Somme]], [[Somme (department)|Somme]], France.<ref name=Times290163a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==28 January==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=28 January 1863 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Actif''\n|flag=Flag unknown\n|desc=The ship foundered on the [[Dogger Bank]]. Her crew were rescued. She was on a voyage from [[Sunderland, County Durham]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] to [[Seville]], Spain.<ref name=Times310163>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Ship News |date=31 January 1863 |page_number=6 |issue=24470 |column=F }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Aeolus''\n|flag={{flag|United States|1861}}\n|desc=The [[brig]] was wrecked on the coast of [[California]], [[Confederate States of America]] {{convert|1.5|nmi|km}} south of the [[Humboldt Bay]] [[Shoal|Bar]].<ref name=gainesp24>Gaines, p. 24.</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Elizabeth''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=[[American Civil War]], [[Union blockade]]: The [[sloop]], a [[Blockade runners of the American Civil War|blockade runner]] carrying a cargo of [[salt]], was captured and burned at the mouth of [[Jupiter Inlet]] on the coast of [[Florida]], Confederate States of America by the [[gunboat]] {{USS|Sagamore|1861|6}} ({{navy|United States|1861}}).<ref name=usnlpcivilwarchronologyJanJun1863/><ref name=gainesp39>Gaines, p. 39.</ref> \n}}<!--Little Dorrit not a loss-->\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Mary Ann''\n|flag=Flag unknown\n|desc=The [[schooner]]-rigged [[Steamship|steamer]] was wrecked on the coast of [[California]] {{convert|1.5|nmi|km}} south of the Humboldt Bay Bar. She was refloated on 29 June.<ref name=gainesp29>Gaines, p. 29.</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Victory''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship collided with ''Brownfield'' ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}) and foundered in the [[North Sea]] off the coast of [[East Riding of Yorkshire|Yorkshire]].<ref name=Times290163a/>\n}}