ergast]]\n| {{Composition bar|20|65|hex={{Australian Labor Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}2\n| 131,083\n| 29.28%\n| {{decrease}}3.0%\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\" |Opposition\n|-\n! align=center| [[1921 Victorian state election|1921]]\n| {{Composition bar|21|65|hex={{Australian Labor Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}1\n| 115,432\n| 34.87%\n| {{increase}}6.4%\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\" |Opposition\n|-\n! align=center| [[1924 Victorian state election|1924]]\n| {{Composition bar|27|65|hex={{Australian Labor Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}6\n|'''128,056'''\n|'''34.87%'''\n| {{steady}}0.0%\n| style=\"background-color:#CCCCFF\" |'''Minority government\n|-\n! align=center| [[1927 Victorian state election|1927]]\n| rowspan=2 | [[Edmond Hogan]]\n| {{Composition bar|28|65|hex={{Australian Labor Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}1\n|'''319,848'''\n|'''41.79%'''\n| {{increase}}6.9%\n| style=\"background-color:#CCCCFF\" |'''Minority government\n|-\n! align=center| [[1929 Victorian state election|1929]]\n| {{Composition bar|30|65|hex={{Australian Labor Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}2\n|'''247,251'''\n|'''39.09%'''\n| {{decrease}}2.7%\n| style=\"background-color:#CCCCFF\" |'''Minority government\n|-\n! align=center| [[1932 Victorian state election|1932]]\n| rowspan=3 | [[Tom Tunnecliffe]]\n| {{Composition bar|16|65|hex={{Australian Labor Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}14\n| 237,993\n| 35.14%\n| {{decrease}}4.0%\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\" |Opposition\n|-\n! align=center| [[1935 Victorian state election|1935]]\n| {{Composition bar|17|65|hex={{Australian Labor Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}1\n| 318,390\n| 37.93%\n| {{increase}}2.8%\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\" |Opposition\n|-\n! align=center| [[1937 Victorian state election|1937]]\n| {{Composition bar|20|65|hex={{Australian Labor Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}3\n| 322,699\n| 41.03%\n| {{increase}}3.1%\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\" |Opposition\n|-\n! 